    <!-- Chosen Palette: "Friendly Nature" - A palette using warm neutrals (beige, brown) with soft, encouraging accents (sky blue, leaf green, sun yellow) to create a friendly, educational, and nature-conscious atmosphere. -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as a single-page, vertical scrolling narrative. The structure is thematic rather than mirroring a formal report. It starts with broad concepts ("What are SDGs?") and narrows down to specific examples ("How Kumagai Gumi helps"). The core is an interactive section where users click on a project type (e.g., Tunnels, Wind Power) and see a visual explanation of how it connects to a specific SDG goal. This direct cause-and-effect interaction is more intuitive and memorable for young learners than charts or dense text. The flow is designed to build understanding step-by-step, from the general to the specific, culminating in a simple, empowering summary. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Instead of data charts, which are too abstract for the target audience, the app uses interactive HTML cards and icons. For instance, clicking the "トンネル" (Tunnel) button (Goal: Organize & Relate) updates a display area to show an explanation and visually highlights SDG 9's icon (Presentation Method: Interactive Diagram). This interaction directly links a concrete action (building a tunnel) to an abstract goal (SDG 9), which is a highly effective teaching method (Justification). All visuals are created using Tailwind CSS and Unicode characters, avoiding complex libraries and focusing on clarity and engagement. This supports the narrative structure and educational goal. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
